[http://r-project.org '''R'''] is a programming language primarily for statistics and numerical analysis.

==Installation==
To see the available USE Flags: <code>emerge -pv R</code><br>
To install: <code> emerge R</code>

==USE Flags==

<code>X</code> = enable X11 output (will want this if you want to view graphs in X)<br>
<code>jpeg</code> = enable jpeg output<br>
<code>png</code> = enable png output<br>
<code>readline</code> = readline support (makes interactive mode behave like bash)<br>
<code>bash-completion</code> = adds tab completion for R in bash<br>
<code>doc</code> = install documentation<br>
<code>tk</code> = enable tk interface and library. Necessary for Rcmdr.<br>

==Integration with Other Programs==

ESS, or Emacs Speaks Statistics, is an Emacs mode that can edit R files and start R from within Emacs.  To install: <code>emerge ess</code>.
